Package: combreg
Type: Package
Title: Bayesian Regression for Combinatorial Response Data
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Yu", "Zheng", email = "seanzhengyu1@gmail.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Bayesian posterior sampling for regression models whose response
    is an integer-valued vector constrained to a polytope defined by a totally
    unimodular system, as in matching and assignment problems. Implements the
    Metropolis-Hastings-within-Gibbs sampler with dual-variable augmentation
    of Zheng et al., with hit-and-run updates for the dual certificates
    accelerated in 'C++', an unconstrained probit baseline for comparison, and
    utilities for constraint validation (total unimodularity, feasibility)
    and data simulation.
